Hakainde Hichilema was arrested on Tuesday and then charged with treason for allegedly obstructing President Edgar Lungu's motorcade. LUSAKA - Zambian police on Thursday denied claims by the main opposition party that its detained leader Hakainde Hichilema had been denied access to his lawyers and family members.&quot;We have not blocked lawyers and Mr Hichilema's members of the family from visiting him because that is his constitutional right,&quot; police spokeswoman Mwaata Katongo said.Hichilema was arrested on Tuesday and then charged with treason for allegedly obstructing President Edgar Lungu's motorcade.